items.title:
io.github.jristretto:testeasypom 25.0.1 发布, JRistrettor tiny portions of Java.

        The 'testeasypom' Parent pom that provides all dependencies that you need for modern testing, generating
        good looking Javadoc and a set of static test reports using spotbugs, pmd, and checkstyle.
        This is NOT cargo-cult, because NONE of the dependencies in this pom will end up in your final product.

        This is a continuation of sebivenlosebipom.
        This project tries to adhere to the development model Tip and  Tail described in JEP 14. (https://openjdk.org/jeps/14)
        There are three tails
        11.0.0 to work with Java version 11 LTS and above
        17.0.0 to work with Java version 17 LTS and above
        21.0.0 to work with Java version 21 LTS and above
        25.0.0 to work with Java version 25 LTS and above

items.title:
org.infinispan:infinispan-spring6-common 16.0.0.Dev04 发布, The Infinispan Spring Integration project provides Spring 6
        integration for Infinispan, a high performance distributed cache.
        Its primary features are

        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager,
        Spring's central caching abstraction, backed by Infinispan's
        EmbeddedCacheManager. To be used if your Spring-powered
        application and Infinispan are colocated, i.e. running within
        the same VM.
        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager
        backed by Infinispan's RemoteCacheManager. To bes used if your
        Spring-powered application accesses Infinispan remotely, i.e.
        over the network.
        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager
        backed by a CacheContainer reference. To be used if your Spring-
        powered application needs access to a CacheContainer defined
        outside the application (e.g. retrieved from JNDI)
        * Spring namespace support allowing shortcut definitions for all the
        components above

        In addition, Infinispan Spring Integration offers various FactoryBeans
        for facilitating creation of Infinispan core classes - Cache, CacheManager,
        ... - within a Spring context.

items.content_text:
org.infinispan:infinispan-spring6-common 16.0.0.Dev04 发布, The Infinispan Spring Integration project provides Spring 6
        integration for Infinispan, a high performance distributed cache.
        Its primary features are

        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager,
        Spring's central caching abstraction, backed by Infinispan's
        EmbeddedCacheManager. To be used if your Spring-powered
        application and Infinispan are colocated, i.e. running within
        the same VM.
        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager
        backed by Infinispan's RemoteCacheManager. To bes used if your
        Spring-powered application accesses Infinispan remotely, i.e.
        over the network.
        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager
        backed by a CacheContainer reference. To be used if your Spring-
        powered application needs access to a CacheContainer defined
        outside the application (e.g. retrieved from JNDI)
        * Spring namespace support allowing shortcut definitions for all the
        components above

        In addition, Infinispan Spring Integration offers various FactoryBeans
        for facilitating creation of Infinispan core classes - Cache, CacheManager,
        ... - within a Spring context.

items.title:
org.infinispan:infinispan-spring6-embedded 16.0.0.Dev04 发布, The Infinispan Spring Integration project provides Spring 6
        integration for Infinispan, a high performance distributed cache.
        Its primary features are

        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager,
        Spring's central caching abstraction, backed by Infinispan's
        EmbeddedCacheManager. To be used if your Spring-powered
        application and Infinispan are colocated, i.e. running within
        the same VM.
        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager
        backed by Infinispan's RemoteCacheManager. To bes used if your
        Spring-powered application accesses Infinispan remotely, i.e.
        over the network.
        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager
        backed by a CacheContainer reference. To be used if your Spring-
        powered application needs access to a CacheContainer defined
        outside the application (e.g. retrieved from JNDI)
        * Spring namespace support allowing shortcut definitions for all the
        components above

        In addition, Infinispan Spring Integration offers various FactoryBeans
        for facilitating creation of Infinispan core classes - Cache, CacheManager,
        ... - within a Spring context.

items.title:
org.infinispan:infinispan-spring6-remote 16.0.0.Dev05 发布, The Infinispan Spring Integration project provides Spring 6
        integration for Infinispan, a high performance distributed cache.
        Its primary features are

        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager,
        Spring's central caching abstraction, backed by Infinispan's
        EmbeddedCacheManager. To be used if your Spring-powered
        application and Infinispan are colocated, i.e. running within
        the same VM.
        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager
        backed by Infinispan's RemoteCacheManager. To bes used if your
        Spring-powered application accesses Infinispan remotely, i.e.
        over the network.
        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager
        backed by a CacheContainer reference. To be used if your Spring-
        powered application needs access to a CacheContainer defined
        outside the application (e.g. retrieved from JNDI)
        * Spring namespace support allowing shortcut definitions for all the
        components above

        In addition, Infinispan Spring Integration offers various FactoryBeans
        for facilitating creation of Infinispan core classes - Cache, CacheManager,
        ... - within a Spring context.

items.title:
org.infinispan:infinispan-spring6-parent 16.0.0.Dev05 发布, The Infinispan Spring Integration project provides Spring 6
        integration for Infinispan, a high performance distributed cache.
        Its primary features are

        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager,
        Spring's central caching abstraction, backed by Infinispan's
        EmbeddedCacheManager. To be used if your Spring-powered
        application and Infinispan are colocated, i.e. running within
        the same VM.
        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager
        backed by Infinispan's RemoteCacheManager. To bes used if your
        Spring-powered application accesses Infinispan remotely, i.e.
        over the network.
        * An implementation of org.springframework.cache.CacheManager
        backed by a CacheContainer reference. To be used if your Spring-
        powered application needs access to a CacheContainer defined
        outside the application (e.g. retrieved from JNDI)
        * Spring namespace support allowing shortcut definitions for all the
        components above

        In addition, Infinispan Spring Integration offers various FactoryBeans
        for facilitating creation of Infinispan core classes - Cache, CacheManager,
        ... - within a Spring context.
